         <text>SAP S/4HANA</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-C8BF7E20-0C2B-4931-B5C7-CE4D04821276" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>L3 Description- 
Create and Maintain Allocations. Setting Volumes across Suppliers</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-E6101B19-F91F-4F7A-B7E1-124ED7ACF1B5" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>IN ECC, quota arrangement is only considered when quota arrangement usage is maintained in the material master and the configuration of quota arrangement includes MRP. In S/4 HANA, quota arrangement usage field is removed, and quota arrangement is always considered by MRP.

Work is reduced as additional parameter that needs to be maintained as we do not have to flag the item in the material master as a quota arrangement relevant material.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-9D40F599-BC69-4B24-B350-B2558371150D" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
